          <avActivityHighlights>Moist avalanches below approximately 1900 m. New snow at elevated altitudes.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>10 to 20 cm of snow, and even more in some localities, will fall until the evening above approximately 1900 m. &lt;br/&gt; The rain will give rise to moistening of the snowpack below approximately 1800 m. &lt;br/&gt; Isolated mostly small dry and moist avalanches are possible as a consequence of the new snow. Avalanches can in some places be released, in particular by large loads. &lt;br/&gt; In regions exposed to heavier precipitation and at elevated altitudes the avalanche prone locations are more widespread and the danger is greater.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>The sleet will give rise to moistening of the snowpack below approximately 1800 m. &lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt; The fresh snow will be rather moist. This snow will be deposited on a crust in particular on sunny slopes. Especially in areas with smaller amounts of fresh snow, this will favour bonding with the old snowpack.</snowpackStructureComment>
